<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="1298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1298">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/7–549: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Scott</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-05">July 5,
                                1949</date>.<lb/>[Received July 6—12:56 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>218. Eighteen Americans, all missionaries, now resident Kulangsu (Amoy)
                            will remain except for family of four soon departing on transfer to
                            Manila. Those in up-country stations also said not evacuating; some
                            visiting Amoy for vacations. Two American male employees Civil Air
                            Transport, families already evacuated, will leave if situation
                            worsens.</p>
                        <p>Consular posters left with Dr. Clarence Holleman, informal head of
                            Colony. Group reports no problems; funds sufficient; relations local
                            authorities very good.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Scott</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>